# `PROJECT_NAME` — Terraform rules

Project identity values referenced below (`PROJECT_NAME`, `PROJECT_SLUG`,
`PROJECT_PACKAGE`) are defined in **`.cursor/rules/constants.mdc`**. Do
not re-declare them.

Apply when authoring, refactoring, or reviewing **Terraform** in this repo.
Terraform configurations are production-grade software: readable, versioned,
testable, and governed by automated policies.

> **Account & region binding (non-negotiable).** Every Terraform plan/apply in
> this repo must target the AWS account, CLI profile, and default region defined in
> **`.cursor/rules/constants.mdc`**, with operational rules in **`.cursor/rules/infra.mdc`**.
> These values enter the stack through **`infra/aws_tf/terraform.tfvars`** (§1.3),
> flow into every module via **`local.solution`** (§1.4), and are enforced by the
> `aws_account_id` variable validation plus `allowed_account_ids` on the
> root `provider "aws"` (§5.3). A plan that would deploy elsewhere must fail.

> **Single Terraform root, single tfvars edit point.** All **`terraform`**
> commands run from **`infra/aws_tf/`**. Runnable `.tf` that participates in
> **plan/apply** lives only under **`infra/aws_tf/`** (root + **`modules/`**).
> Users edit **`infra/aws_tf/terraform.tfvars`** for root input values (§1.3);
> every other root `.tf` file is locked structure. A parallel
> **`infra/deployed/aws/<account>/<region>/services/<service>/`** tree maps
> **ownership** (including **Helm** charts and optional **`terraform/aws/<primitive>/`**
> markers); it is **not** a second Terraform root — see **`.cursor/rules/infra.mdc`**.

---

## 1. Code organization and structure

Organize Terraform code for clarity, reusability, and environment isolation.

### 1.1 Project layout

All **runnable** Terraform in this repo lives under **`infra/aws_tf/`** — a single root
module that orchestrates one or more reusable child modules under
`infra/aws_tf/modules/`. There are **no** sibling `environments/dev`,
`environments/prod` directories; environment switching is handled by changing
values in **`terraform.tfvars`** (the sole user-edit file — see §1.3), not by
duplicating directories.

**Deployed map (documentation + Helm, not a second root):** under
**`infra/deployed/aws/<AWS_ACCOUNT_ID>/<region>/services/`**, each **`frontend`**, **`iam.service`**, or **`solutions.svc`**
folder may contain **`helm/<chart>/`** (real charts) and **`terraform/aws/<primitive>/`**
(markers such as **`.gitkeep`** showing which service owns which AWS surface).
Agents **must** place module **source code** under **`infra/aws_tf/modules/`** and wire it from **`infra/aws_tf/main.tf`**.
Skills copy reusable HCL **from** **`infra/tf_lib/`** **into** **`infra/aws_tf/modules/`** — never run `terraform` against `tf_lib` or `deployed/` paths.

BAD — monolithic `main.tf` or resources scattered across ad-hoc folders:

```terraform
# infra/main.tf
resource "aws_vpc" "vpc" { /* ... */ }
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "logs" { /* ... */ }
# Mixed concerns, no module boundary, no input surface
```

GOOD — single root under `infra/aws_tf/` with composable child modules, plus optional deployed mirror:

```
infra/
├── aws_tf/                    # ONLY tree where `terraform init/plan/apply` runs
│   ├── main.tf                # root module: composes child modules only
│   ├── variables.tf           # input variable DECLARATIONS (locked structure)
│   ├── terraform.tfvars       # input VALUES — the ONLY file users edit (§1.3)
│   ├── outputs.tf             # root outputs (alphabetically sorted)
│   ├── providers.tf           # required_version, required_providers, provider "aws"
│   ├── backend.tf             # remote state (S3 + `use_lockfile` native lock)
│   ├── locals.tf              # locals — including `local.solution` (§1.4)
│   ├── versions.tf            # optional split of the terraform { ... } block
│   └── modules/
│       ├── vpc/
│       │   ├── main.tf
│       │   ├── variables.tf # must accept `var.solution` (§1.4)
│       │   └── outputs.tf
│       └── s3_bucket/
│           ├── main.tf
│           ├── variables.tf # must accept `var.solution` (§1.4)
│           └── outputs.tf
└── deployed/aws/<account>/<region>/
    └── services/<service>/
        ├── helm/<chart>/      # Helm charts (Kubernetes), not Terraform state
        └── terraform/aws/<primitive>/  # ownership markers — no nested terraform root
```

**Canonical templates (not an apply root):** **`infra/tf_lib/s3`** and **`infra/tf_lib/dynamodb`**
are skill-maintained **copies** of module layouts. New infrastructure **modules** belong under **`infra/aws_tf/modules/`** after copy + edit.

All `terraform` commands run from `infra/aws_tf/`:

```bash
cd infra/aws_tf
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply
```

### 1.2 Standard file naming

Use HashiCorp's recommended file names for consistency. Files marked
**user-editable** are the *only* ones a non-platform engineer should change.

| File | Purpose | User-editable? |
|------|---------|----------------|
| `backend.tf` | Remote state configuration (S3 + DynamoDB). | No |
| `main.tf` | Root module composition: calls into `modules/*`. No raw resources. | No |
| `outputs.tf` | All `output` blocks, alphabetically sorted. | No |
| `providers.tf` | `terraform { required_version, required_providers }` and `provider "aws"`. | No |
| `variables.tf` | All `variable` block **declarations** (types, validation, descriptions), alphabetically sorted. | No |
| `locals.tf` | Local values, including the `solution` object (§1.4). | No |
| `versions.tf` | Optional split of the `terraform { ... }` block. | No |
| **`terraform.tfvars`** | **All input VALUES** — solution metadata, account, region. | **Yes — sole edit point (§1.3).** |

### 1.3 Input parameters — the sole user-edit boundary

`infra/aws_tf/terraform.tfvars` is the **only** file the user is expected to
edit to provision this stack correctly. Every other `.tf` file in the root
module is locked structure maintained by platform engineers.

**Required inputs** (declare in `variables.tf`, supply values in `terraform.tfvars`):

| Variable | Type | Purpose | Default |
|----------|------|---------|---------|
| `solution_name` | `string` | Short slug for the solution (`lower_snake_case`). | — |
| `solution_description` | `string` | Human-readable description of what this stack provisions. | — |
| `solution_version` | `string` | Semver release of this infrastructure (e.g. `"0.1.0"`). | — |
| `solution_date` | `string` | ISO-8601 release date of this version (`YYYY-MM-DD`). | — |
| `aws_account_id` | `string` | AWS account this stack deploys into. | Must equal `AWS_ACCOUNT_ID` in **`constants.mdc`**. |
| `aws_region` | `string` | AWS region this stack deploys into. | Must equal `AWS_DEFAULT_REGION` in **`constants.mdc`**. |

`aws_account_id` and `aws_region` are pre-filled to satisfy the repo-wide
account binding in `.cursor/rules/infra.mdc`. They must **never** be changed
without an explicit per-turn user override in the same way `infra.mdc`
governs CLI calls.

**`variables.tf` — locked declarations with validation:**

```terraform
variable "solution_name" {
  description = "Short slug for the solution (lower_snake_case)."
  type        = string
  nullable    = false
  validation {
    condition     = can(regex("^[a-z][a-z0-9_]*$", var.solution_name))
    error_message = "solution_name must be lower_snake_case starting with a letter."
  }
}

variable "solution_description" {
  description = "Human-readable description of what this stack provisions."
  type        = string
  nullable    = false
}

variable "solution_version" {
  description = "Semantic version (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH) of this infrastructure release."
  type        = string
  nullable    = false
  validation {
    condition     = can(regex("^[0-9]+\\.[0-9]+\\.[0-9]+$", var.solution_version))
    error_message = "solution_version must be semver, e.g. 0.1.0."
  }
}

variable "solution_date" {
  description = "ISO-8601 (YYYY-MM-DD) release date of this version."
  type        = string
  nullable    = false
  validation {
    condition     = can(regex("^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$", var.solution_date))
    error_message = "solution_date must be YYYY-MM-DD."
  }
}

variable "aws_account_id" {
  description = "AWS account ID this stack deploys into. Must equal 017868795096 (see infra.mdc)."
  type        = string
  default     = "017868795096"
  nullable    = false
  validation {
    condition     = var.aws_account_id == "017868795096"
    error_message = "Account binding violated: this repo deploys only to 017868795096."
  }
}

variable "aws_region" {
  description = "AWS region this stack deploys into."
  type        = string
  default     = "us-east-1"
  nullable    = false
}
```

**`terraform.tfvars` — the sole user-editable file:**

```terraform
# infra/aws_tf/terraform.tfvars
# THE ONLY FILE A USER EDITS. All other .tf files are locked structure.

solution_name        = "arb_ai_assistant" # = PROJECT_PACKAGE from constants.mdc
solution_description = "ARB - AI Assistant primary AWS infrastructure." # = PROJECT_NAME from constants.mdc
solution_version     = "0.1.0"
solution_date        = "2026-05-16"

# Account binding — DO NOT change without an explicit per-turn override.
aws_account_id = "017868795096"
aws_region     = "us-east-1"
```

### 1.4 Solution metadata propagation

The six root inputs above are bundled into a single immutable `local.solution`
object and passed to **every** child module as a single `solution` variable.
This guarantees the same identity, account, and region flow through every
resource without per-module duplication.

**`locals.tf` (root):**

```terraform
locals {
  solution = {
    name        = var.solution_name
    description = var.solution_description
    version     = var.solution_version
    date        = var.solution_date
    account_id  = var.aws_account_id
    region      = var.aws_region
  }
}
```

**`main.tf` (root) — every child module receives `solution`:**

```terraform
module "vpc" {
  source   = "./modules/vpc"
  solution = local.solution

  # module-specific inputs only
  vpc_cidr = "10.0.0.0/16"
}

module "s3_logs" {
  source   = "./modules/s3_bucket"
  solution = local.solution

  bucket_purpose = "logs"
}
```

**Every child module — `modules/<name>/variables.tf` — declares the
contract once:**

```terraform
variable "solution" {
  description = "Solution-wide metadata propagated from the root module (see root variables.tf)."
  type = object({
    name        = string
    description = string
    version     = string
    date        = string
    account_id  = string
    region      = string
  })
  nullable = false
}
```

Child modules **must not** redeclare `solution_name`, `aws_region`, etc. as
separate top-level variables; read them off `var.solution` so the contract
stays in one place.

**Agent skills (S3 / DynamoDB):** guided skills under **`.cursor/skills/`** copy templates from **`infra/tf_lib/`** into **`infra/aws_tf/modules/<name>/`**, add **`module`** blocks to **`infra/aws_tf/main.tf`**, and should pass **`solution = local.solution`** at the root unless the user explicitly needs a different object. Update **`infra/deployed/.../services/<service>/terraform/aws/<primitive>/`** markers per **`.cursor/rules/infra.mdc`**.

