## 6. Security and configuration management

### 6.1 Secrets management

**Never** hardcode sensitive data in `.tf`, `.tfvars`, or state-adjacent
artifacts. Fetch dynamically from AWS Secrets Manager / SSM Parameter Store
(or HashiCorp Vault), and mark values `sensitive = true` where they flow
through variables or outputs.

BAD:

```terraform
resource "aws_db_instance" "app_db" {
  password = "SuperSecretPassword123!" # NEVER
}
```

GOOD:

```terraform
data "aws_secretsmanager_secret_version" "db_creds" {
  secret_id = "prod/arb-ai-assistant/db-credentials" # PROJECT_SLUG-prefixed
}

locals {
  db_credentials = jsondecode(data.aws_secretsmanager_secret_version.db_creds.secret_string)
}

resource "aws_db_instance" "app_db" {
  password = local.db_credentials.password
}
```

### 6.2 Policy as code

Integrate Open Policy Agent (OPA / Conftest) or HashiCorp Sentinel into CI to
enforce org policy (encryption, tagging, public access bans, account binding)
**before** apply.

